BEGIN_TEXT
A \(0.20\)-kg billiard ball bounces back and forth without losing its energy between the cushions of a \(1.5\) m long table.
$BR
$BR

a) If the ball is in its ground state, how many years does it need to get from one cushion to the other? You may compare this time interval to the age of the universe.
$BR
$BR

\{ans_rule(40)\} \(\times 10^{26}\) years
$BR
$BR

b) How much energy is required to make the ball go from its ground state to its first excited state?
$BR
$BR

\{ans_rule(40)\} \(\times 10^{-66}\) J
$BR
$BR

END_TEXT

